-- Lindsey Vonn of U.S. Captures Fourth Overall World Cup Skiing Championship
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-03-09T13:34:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-09/lindsey-vonn-of-u-s-captures-fourth-overall-world-cup-skiing-championship.html
Lindsey Vonn  clinched her fourth
overall World Cup skiing championship by winning today’s giant
slalom race in Are,  Sweden .  Vonn’s 52nd career victory gives her an unbeatable 554-
points lead over Slovenia’s  Tina Maze  with five races, worth a
maximum 500 points, left in the season.  The victory also moves Vonn, 27, past Phil Mahre for the most
overall World Cup titles by an American.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  